      • setNextChannel

        private void setNextChannel​(java.lang.String channel,
                            int inputFlitIndex)
        Selects the next channel whose flit will be taken from the front of the list, following a Round Robin order, and checking if the channel actually exists and has a flit in it

        Also takes into account if the flit is part of a packet, sending keeping flits of a packet together as they move through the pipeline

        Parameters:
        channel - The current channel that's next in order
        inputFlitIndex - The index of the flit within the packet

      • clearPipelineSlots
